<cherrytree>
	<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Introduction" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527505581.06" ts_lastsave="1527505592.55" unique_id="1">
		<rich_text></rich_text>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Genre" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527505592.55" ts_lastsave="1527506060.5" unique_id="2">
			<rich_text>To Glory and Beyond is a randomly generated turn-based rogue-lite</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Description" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527505679.14" ts_lastsave="1527613647.82" unique_id="3">
			<rich_text>In To Glory and Beyond, the player takes control of a Party of adventurers on a quest to vanquish the Evil of the land.

A game consists of building a party, setting out on an adventure to defeat an Evil and finally either Victory or Defeat.

Regardless of outcome, the game will have lasting impact on the players upcoming attempts. In Victory, the characters that survive become Legends</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Presentation and Visuals" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527505907.05" ts_lastsave="1527506289.99" unique_id="4">
			<rich_text>The game is separated into three different screens, Management, World and Battle.</rich_text>
			<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Management" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527505950.6" ts_lastsave="1527505953.22" unique_id="5">
				<rich_text>Management screens are menus where the player assembles parties, read descriptions, shop.

These are done in text boxes with sprite visuals to aid in describing what the player is doing.</rich_text>
			</node>
			<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="World" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506044.61" ts_lastsave="1527506571.57" unique_id="6">
				<rich_text>The World map is a randomly generated grid of square tiles, with each tile having a biome and a possible feature.</rich_text>
			</node>
			<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Battle" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506571.57" ts_lastsave="1527506807.76" unique_id="9">
				<rich_text>When the player enters Battle, they are presented with a new grid of randomly generated tiles.

What kind of tiles depends on where the battle is taking place, with locations such as forests, in a town or inside a dungeon being some examples.</rich_text>
			</node>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Gameplay" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506289.99" ts_lastsave="1527506295.83" unique_id="7">
			<rich_text></rich_text>
			<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="The World Map" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506306.29" ts_lastsave="1527507339.01" unique_id="8">
				<rich_text>This map is traversed by the player via an Avatar that represents their Party. They will have random encounters, visit towns, complete quests and prepare in whatever way they can for the Final Confrontation.</rich_text>
				<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Biomes" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527507339.01" ts_lastsave="1527507494.52" unique_id="14">
