			<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Battle" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506907.95" ts_lastsave="1527506960.57" unique_id="10">
				<rich_text></rich_text>
				<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Setup" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527506957.24" ts_lastsave="1527530093.21" unique_id="11">
					<rich_text>When battle begins, the player first gets to set up their party on the battle map.

There are different states the player can be brought into battle in; Ambush!, Surrounded! and Confrontation!.

The enemy characters are always shown to be placed on the grid before the player has to deploy their own party.</rich_text>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Ambush!" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527507040.92" ts_lastsave="1527508427.68" unique_id="12">
						<rich_text>If the encounter is an Ambush!, the enemy has to deploy in the center of the battleground, while the player can deploy anywhere along the perimeter of the arena.</rich_text>
					</node>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Surrounded!" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527507044.13" ts_lastsave="1527508444.03" unique_id="13">
						<rich_text>The opposite of Ambush!. The player has to deploy their group near the center of the arena while the enemy can be found surrounding them.</rich_text>
					</node>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Confrontation!" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527507056.82" ts_lastsave="1527508483.58" unique_id="15">
						<rich_text>In a Confrontation!, both parties are located on opposite sides of the battleground.</rich_text>
					</node>
				</node>
				<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Turn Breakdown" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527530093.21" ts_lastsave="1527537993.27" unique_id="27">
					<rich_text>The battle is played out in a turn order, with each turn divided into three distinct phases; Enemy Turn, Player Turn, Turn Resolution


with the opponent beginning each turn by moving their characters and preparing their attack.

This is followed by the player acting out their entire turn, moving their party and attacking/casting spells/activating abilities.

After the player is done, all enemy characters resolve their attacks and abilities in their designated order.</rich_text>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Enemy Turn" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527537993.27" ts_lastsave="1527538008.38" unique_id="28">
						<rich_text>All enemy characters move and then aim and prepare their action.</rich_text>
					</node>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Player Turn" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527537996.73" ts_lastsave="1527538030.76" unique_id="29">
						<rich_text>The player gets to control all their units in any order of their liking, and then</rich_text>
					</node>
					<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Turn Resolution" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" ts_creation="1527538000.74" ts_lastsave="1527538000.74" unique_id="30">
						<rich_text></rich_text>
					</node>
				</node>
			</node>
